Pathological pain conditions are generally categorized into (1) inflammatory pain following tissue injury, (2) cancer pain, (3) neuropathic pain following nerve, spinal cord or brain injury, and (4) drug-induced pain.Major cell types involved in pain in the DRG.Local sympathetic blockade or lesion is commonly used to treat certain pain conditions including complex regional pain syndrome, phantom limb pain, postherpetic neuralgia, ischemic pain, cancer pain, skeletal pain and arthritis pain [111, 112].The sympathetic nerve sprouting can affect not only DRG neurons, but also glia and immune cells.
